726240f-a.title: Queens: Broadway - Vernon Boulevard
726240f-a.text:
Broadway, at the N. E. corner of Vernon Boulevard, showing an
old farmhouse, dating back to pre-Revolutionary days. Eugene L.
Armbruster states that this may have been Mayor Henry Debevoise's
house, but that some disagreement exists whether it actually was.
It was owned by Miss Bragar in 1841, and by C. W. Strang in 1873.
P. Bartlett was the owner in 1896.
Views 1,2: May, 1923
Views 3,4: April, 1925
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
MAY BE REPRODUCED
